President Donald J. Trump has declared a state of emergency in South Carolina due to the emergency conditions caused by Hurricane Dorian. This declaration allows the Department of Homeland Security and the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to coordinate relief efforts to help the local population. FEMA is authorized to provide equipment and resources to alleviate the impacts of the emergency, and emergency protective measures will be provided at 75 percent federal funding. Allan Jarvis has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.